WHEREAS, in 2024, NHC Cookeville was named an NHC 5-Star Center of Excellence,
had a Patient Care Component of 95.66 percent, overall occupancy of 94.56 percent, and a net
customer satisfaction score of 76.62; and
WHEREAS, additionally, NHC Cookeville is recognized as a CMS 5-Star Center,
indicating that it is in the top ten percent of all skilled nursing centers; and
WHEREAS, this State places a high priority on the provision of competent and
compassionate care in all assisted living and long-term care facilities, and it is fitting that this
General Assembly should recognize and applaud NHC Cookeville and its staff for their
extraordinary professionalism; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor NHC Cookeville on being named the 2024 Center of the
Year and applaud the staff and administrators for their ongoing commitment to providing
outstanding care to the residents of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
